### Purpose
PR adds new Endpoints to java client for getting, adding and removing data from data measures. 

1. Initialize Client 
``` java
StreamPipesClient client = StreamPipesClient
                .create(<URI>,<PORT>, StreamPipesCredentials.withApiKey(<USER>, <KEY>),true);
DataLakeResourceApi dataLakeResourceApi = client.dataLakeResourceApi();
``` 
2. Get Data from Measure 
``` java
dataLakeResourceApi.get(<measureName>, new HashMap<>());
``` 
HashMap takes additional filtering arguments, e.g.  startDate or endDate 
4. Change/add Data to Measure
``` java
String data_man = "[\n" +
                "  {\n" +
                 "    \"timestamp\": 1765290723327,\n" +
                "    \"density\": 60.0,\n" +
                "    \"mass_flow\": 10.0,\n" +
                "    \"sensorId\": \"a\",\n" +
                "    \"sensor_fault_flags\": false,\n" +
                "    \"temperature\": 0.0,\n" +
                "    \"volume_flow\": 0.0\n" +
                "  }\n" +
                "]";
var tags = new TreeMap<String, String>();
tags.put("sensorId","a");
 SpQueryResult queryResult = null;
 try{

   queryResult = SpQuerySerializer.processJsonDataWithTags(data_man, tags);}
 catch(Exception e){
    System.out.println(e.getMessage());
 }
dataLakeResourceApi.update(<measureName>, queryResult, <schemaMismatch>); 
``` 

Overwrites if timestamp exists, otherwise generate a new entry. Tags can be null but need to be set to enable influx groupBy.
6. Delete Data 
``` java
dataLakeResourceApi.delete(<measureName>,<startTimestamp>,<endTimestamp>);
``` 

